      <h1>How to Choose a Financial Advisor: Fees, Types, and Red Flags</h1>
      <p class="article-intro">Choosing the right financial advisor can add hundreds of thousands of dollars to your lifetime wealth — or cost you just as much if you choose poorly. The financial advisory industry is crowded with different titles, compensation models, regulatory standards, and credentials, making it genuinely difficult for consumers to distinguish advisors who act in their best interest from those who prioritize their own commission income. This guide cuts through the confusion by explaining every type of advisor, how each one gets paid, what credentials actually matter, which questions to ask before hiring, and which red flags should send you running.</p>
    </header>

